	   <tr><td colspan=2>I would have to say don't charge for buffs or heals when you are in a group; otherwise no one will want to let you join into a group especially if you want to "charge" them for letting you join.... The only exception might be the Symbol line as that requires a reagent. <br><br>Ask for donations for binding... sure thats fair game, But to charge other people for buffs, heals, or to join their group?... No. Don't do it.<br><br>I strongly disagree with that strategy. It's up to you but &lt;shakes head&gt; I feel that you're going about it (gaining money) the wrong way.<br><br>A good group will get you items and coins... Solo will get you dead, and speaking for myself, I would not accept a member into a group who "charges" for their spells. We all bring various strengths to a group. Ours is buffs and heals, with some melee. Others bring different skills. <br><br>As a question, If you charge them for your spells, do they charge you for theirs? If they do, how do you determine how much to pay? And to whom?&nbsp;&nbsp;Nope, I feel you're going about it the wrong way.<br><br><br>Durus Stoneguard<br>Initiate of the 34th Mystery of Brell Serilis<br>Povar<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
